Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses parallelization and thread distribution for matrix multiplication on GPUs.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on optimizing performance on Nvidia Volta GPGPUs.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is relevant as the paper deals with matrix-matrix multiplication and autotuning for optimal performance.
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is relevant as the paper discusses code generation for a specialized implementation.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses a flexible and configurable mapping scheme for the implementation.
